<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-ChXdXn7C9jk24rt4MLmvng" name="dev_test_plan,_l0zlwLXtEd-FofslSzycTA" guid="-ChXdXn7C9jk24rt4MLmvng" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>This task creates the unit test plan or suite based upon the context of the model being built in the current activity. The&#xD;
model could be the Platform Independent Model or the Platform Specific Model.</mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_0gymcOCJEd-aE9U0mRj03A" name="Create test plan organization" guid="_0gymcOCJEd-aE9U0mRj03A">
    <sectionDescription>Define the organization structure you will use in the test plan i.e. chapters, sections, index, etc.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_10-yMOCJEd-aE9U0mRj03A" name="Add Test Cases to test suite" guid="_10-yMOCJEd-aE9U0mRj03A">
    <sectionDescription>Each test case should include preconditions, data, test flow, and expected results.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_3Y0jgOCJEd-aE9U0mRj03A" name="Add &quot;verify&quot; traceability from test cases to requirements" guid="_3Y0jgOCJEd-aE9U0mRj03A">
    <sectionDescription>It is important to establish traceability from the test case to the requirement as soon as you write the test case.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_6AwPEOCJEd-aE9U0mRj03A" name="Perform coverage analysis to ensure test case coverage is adequate" guid="_6AwPEOCJEd-aE9U0mRj03A">
    <sectionDescription>This is very difficult to do by hand.&amp;nbsp; It is best to perform coverage analysis using test coverage tools.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_-WguYOCJEd-aE9U0mRj03A" name="Specify tester steps required for test execution" guid="_-WguYOCJEd-aE9U0mRj03A">
    <sectionDescription>The tester must know how to set up, perform, and analyze the test execution.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>The purpose of this task is to create a test plan that depicts the approach, scope and content of a test suite.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
